definitions.definition: A removal , especially of a ruler or government , by force or threat of force; usurpation .
( archaic , rare ) An act of throwing something to the ground ; an overturning .

main_definition: A removal , especially of a ruler or government , by force or threat of force; usurpation .
secondary_definitions: ( archaic , rare ) An act of throwing something to the ground ; an overturning .

definitions.definition: A throw that goes too far .
examples: He overthrew the ball and it went for four runs.

subdefinitions.definition: A run scored by the batting side when a fielder throws the ball back to the infield , whence it continues to the opposite outfield .

main_definition: ( sports ) A throw that goes too far .
